This paper deals with the analysis of combinatorial auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the communication complexity of the equilibrium, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper analyzes the economic efficiency of the bundling equilibrium, which falls under the category of computational economics (cs.EC).
